class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="savvy-homemade" class="entry-website-title">Savvy Homemade</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-3840x16254-2024072.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-3840x16254-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-3840x16254-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Savvy Homemade"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.savvyhomemade.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.savvyhomemade.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Dorset, England, U.K.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Savvy Homemade is a website that showcases tried-and-tested DIY crafts and products in various categories, including beauty, skincare, and wellness. The website combines soft color accents with plenty of high-quality color images accompanying various page links to capture the company's refined aesthetic.</p><p>Thanks to the easy-to-navigate content categories and a helpful search bar, visitors can peruse the site's latest product reviews, crafting recipes, DIY workshops, and related blog posts. The "Shop My Ingredients" page takes users to the company's affiliate page on Amazon, which is discussed in its "Affiliate Disclosure" section.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site features a good balance of text and images to ensure the extensive lists of articles don't become overwhelming. The addition of various customer testimonials and a "Featured On" section helps strengthen the website's credibility.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE picked up several contrast errors throughout the site and accessScan notes that the website is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies. The advertisement pop-ups at the bottom of the site feel slightly distracting.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-3840x16254-2024072.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-3840x16254-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop website ensures good visual engagement with well-organized page layouts that draw the eye to the wide variety of content categories. However, the lack of favored navigation options like a floating top menu and back-to-top button are noticeable, hampering the overall user experience.</p><p>Prominent CTA buttons are missing from the website, and their use would ensure customers engage with the site's free courses, membership options, and shopping links.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-824x16382-2024072.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-savvy-homemade-824x16382-2024072.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On mobile, the website performs well with fast page loading times and an optimal performance score of 98/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test. The smaller screen remains uncrowded with lots of white space and prominent headings, but as with the desktop version, the mobile site would benefit from clear CTA buttons. The search bar icon should also be enlarged to aid readability.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="organically-becca" class="entry-website-title">Organically Becca</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-3840x12515-2024072.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-3840x12515-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-3840x12515-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Organically Becca"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://organicallybecca.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://organicallybecca.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Milwaukee, Wisconsin, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Organically Becca is a blog that provides insights on organic living and holistic wellness, as well as product reviews and affiliate links to the blogger's ShopMy and Amazon storefronts. The website has a harmonious aesthetic with earthy colors and high-resolution images that effectively capture the blog's theme of balance.</p><p>Visitors can peruse a wide range of #OrganicallyBeccaApproved products across various categories, access discount codes on certain products, or book an individual beauty consultation with the blogger. However, driving customers to these options could be improved with more prominent CTA buttons.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The "About" page features an introductory video of the blogger expanding on the website's commitment to green and organic living. The site also has a "freebies library" that gives visitors access to free PDF digital downloads, including shopping guides and beauty directories.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE indicated a large number of insufficient contrast ratios across the website. While the top menu bar is prominent, clear CTA buttons are missing to funnel visitors to the blog's contact options and its consultation booking form. The site's affiliate disclosure is also difficult to find and hidden in the "Terms" page.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-3840x12515-2024072.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-3840x12515-2024072.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop version presents the website's content-rich pages beautifully with lots of white space and colorful accents that draw the eye in. On desktop, the large headings ensure a good reading experience, but the body text is quite small and difficult to read against some of the colorful backgrounds. According to Google's PageSpeed Insights test, the website has optimal performance and SEO scoring 99/100 and 100/100 respectively.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-824x15547-2024072.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-organically-becca-824x15547-2024072.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>On mobile, the website's text is easier to read and more digestible when slimmed down, enhancing the overall user experience. However, the search bar gets hidden behind the hamburger menu, and the lack of prominent CTA buttons in the top menu bar is noticeable. Performance-wise, the site's pages load fairly quickly and its performance score was 70/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights test.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
